1
00:00:07,440 --> 00:00:11,399
<i>...nails Harrison, and drags him down
as if he were gonna hog-tie him, too.</i>

2
00:00:11,600 --> 00:00:13,318
<i>JB Logan helped out.</i>

3
00:00:13,520 --> 00:00:17,308
<i>Anderson's ninth tackle,
he has two behind the line of scrimmage.</i>

4
00:00:17,520 --> 00:00:19,875
<i>Give Harrison four yards
to the twenty-six.</i>

5
00:00:20,080 --> 00:00:23,152
<i>Stoney Walker's coming in
and Rufus Middleton is going out,</i>

6
00:00:23,360 --> 00:00:24,793
<i>giving Middleton a breather.</i>

7
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:28,515
<i>Boy, has he been burning up
a few miles today on stadium turf.</i>

8
00:00:28,720 --> 00:00:31,871
<i>Rufus Middleton. All right,
it's second and six on the twenty-six.</i>

9
00:00:32,080 --> 00:00:36,312
<i>Stoney Walker deployed wide right, Larry
Singer left. The line is set. The snap...</i>

10
00:00:36,520 --> 00:00:39,273
How long do we have to keep
watching this crap?

11
00:00:39,480 --> 00:00:41,835
<i>...tumbled down
on the twenty-three. A quick trap.</i>

12
00:00:42,040 --> 00:00:45,430
<i>He had room to run except
for that man from Jacksonville,</i>

13
00:00:45,640 --> 00:00:49,474
<i>James Washington La Croix,
who made a good, sure, low tackle,</i>

14
00:00:49,680 --> 00:00:52,592
<i>just as Harrison was about to spurt
deep into the secondary.</i>

15
00:00:52,800 --> 00:00:55,519
<i>We've had quite an exciting
ball game this afternoon...</i>

16
00:00:55,720 --> 00:01:01,317
Only a moron could sit and watch
two football games one after the other.

17
00:01:01,520 --> 00:01:03,750
<i>Victorio covers him there.
Singer left.</i>

18
00:01:03,960 --> 00:01:05,837
<i>It's about time
Robinson went to Singer.</i>

19
00:01:06,040 --> 00:01:08,679
<i>Harrison and Mancuso
are split behind Robinson.</i>

20
00:01:08,880 --> 00:01:11,553
<i>Robinson gives instead to Harrison,
up the middle again.</i>

21
00:01:11,760 --> 00:01:14,991
<i>He may have the first down,
he's close to the 20-yard line.</i>

22
00:01:15,200 --> 00:01:16,997
<i>Let's see where they mark the ball.</i>

23
00:01:17,200 --> 00:01:21,751
<i>Billy Jacoby and Sonny Anderson again
making the tackle. It's going to be...</i>

24
00:01:21,960 --> 00:01:25,111
Thank God.

25
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:31,994
That feels so good.
I feel so relaxed.

26
00:01:32,880 --> 00:01:35,155
You know the help is off, Crewe.

27
00:01:35,360 --> 00:01:37,191
The phones are off.

28
00:01:38,280 --> 00:01:39,872
We're all alone.

29
00:01:42,240 --> 00:01:45,630
Let's get it on, honey. Come on.

30
00:01:46,680 --> 00:01:49,752
- Honey.
- What?

31
00:01:49,960 --> 00:01:54,112
Wake up, baby. Come on.
You know it'll be good.

32
00:01:54,320 --> 00:01:57,869
You know how good it is.
Come on, Crewe.

33
00:01:58,080 --> 00:01:59,911
Get off me!

34
00:02:02,160 --> 00:02:04,799
Son of a bitch.

35
00:02:13,240 --> 00:02:14,832
Where are you going?

36
00:02:15,760 --> 00:02:18,957
- Splitting.
- Splitting?

37
00:02:19,160 --> 00:02:23,950
You split when I tell you to split,
you All-American son of a bitch.

38
00:02:24,160 --> 00:02:25,991
Lovely, lovely.

39
00:02:29,440 --> 00:02:32,113
And when you walk out, stay out.

40
00:02:32,320 --> 00:02:34,595
You're too expensive to be useless.

41
00:02:39,720 --> 00:02:40,994
Whore!

42
00:02:42,040 --> 00:02:48,434
- That's exactly what you are, a whore.
- I never looked at it that way before.

43
00:02:48,640 --> 00:02:50,517
Everybody's bought you.

44
00:02:50,720 --> 00:02:54,030
Colleges, the pros, your gamblers.

45
00:02:54,240 --> 00:02:56,470
Who bought those
beautiful caps on your teeth,

46
00:02:56,680 --> 00:02:59,399
the clothes you're wearing
and the bloody tan you've got?

47
00:02:59,600 --> 00:03:01,033
Me!

48
00:03:02,280 --> 00:03:05,431
Have I ever neglected to thank you,
Melissa?

49
00:03:05,640 --> 00:03:07,278
You has-been.

50
00:03:07,760 --> 00:03:09,034
Where're your keys?

51
00:03:09,240 --> 00:03:13,119
If I took everything back... Forget
my keys! You'd be bare-assed naked.

52
00:03:13,320 --> 00:03:17,233
- Where're your goddamn keys?
- Don't touch my keys.

53
00:03:20,160 --> 00:03:22,993
I think the love
has gone out of our relationship.

54
00:03:23,200 --> 00:03:24,633
Bastard.

55
00:03:26,600 --> 00:03:29,034
Don't you take my Masseratti.

56
00:03:29,240 --> 00:03:31,470
I earned it.

57
00:03:35,640 --> 00:03:39,428
I told you not to touch
my goddamn car!

58
00:04:13,960 --> 00:04:15,234
Police.

59
00:07:00,920 --> 00:07:06,358
- Do you have a driver's licence?
- What, are you taking a poll?

60
00:07:08,480 --> 00:07:11,950
Well, look what we got here.
A miniature cop.

61
00:07:14,840 --> 00:07:16,512
Can we see your driver's licence?

62
00:07:17,360 --> 00:07:18,634
What?

63
00:07:18,840 --> 00:07:21,149
Can we see your driver's licence?

64
00:07:21,360 --> 00:07:24,432
See if I can get it out.

65
00:07:29,520 --> 00:07:30,919
It's him all right.

66
00:07:31,120 --> 00:07:33,076
Why'd you dump her car in the Bay?

67
00:07:33,280 --> 00:07:36,078
- What?
- Why'd you dump her car in the Bay?

68
00:07:36,280 --> 00:07:38,840
I couldn't find a car wash.

69
00:07:47,840 --> 00:07:49,398
Step away from the bar.

70
00:07:51,240 --> 00:07:53,834
Mister, step away from the bar!

71
00:07:54,040 --> 00:07:56,793
Don't get pushy, cowboy.

72
00:08:00,960 --> 00:08:03,554
- Turn it around.
- Come on!

73
00:08:10,400 --> 00:08:13,233
- Hold that son of a bitch!
- Damn!

74
00:08:13,440 --> 00:08:17,319
Now we got you
for stealing a car, drunken driving,

75
00:08:17,520 --> 00:08:20,159
drunk in public and resisting arrest.

76
00:08:22,400 --> 00:08:26,871
- Want something else?
- Yeah. I'm going to make you taller.

77
00:09:12,160 --> 00:09:14,037
OK, men, let's go.

78
00:09:38,040 --> 00:09:39,996
Good afternoon.
Where are you from?

79
00:09:40,200 --> 00:09:43,749
- Palm Beach County.
- Thank you, sir. Second door down.

80
00:09:44,360 --> 00:09:45,634
This way, men.

81
00:09:45,840 --> 00:09:49,628
They gave you $10,000
for shaving off your moustache on TV?

82
00:09:52,600 --> 00:09:55,068
How about giving me $5,000 worth?

83
00:09:56,840 --> 00:10:02,198
Coming right off: There's about
twenty-five hundred, three thousand,

84
00:10:02,400 --> 00:10:04,038
four thousand coming up,

85
00:10:04,240 --> 00:10:06,515
five thousand!

86
00:10:17,400 --> 00:10:19,960
- Anything else, sir?
- That's it.

87
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:05,719
Warden Hazen thinks
you're pretty hot stuff.

88
00:11:06,880 --> 00:11:09,348
But I'm Captain Knauer.

89
00:11:09,560 --> 00:11:13,792
I'm going to spell
things out for you. I run this prison.

90
00:11:14,440 --> 00:11:17,193
He sits there growing old.
I'm out here busting heads.

91
00:11:18,080 --> 00:11:19,991
And I run the football team.

92
00:11:20,440 --> 00:11:23,113
- What football team?
- My football team.

93
00:11:24,000 --> 00:11:25,274
Oh.

94
00:11:26,080 --> 00:11:28,913
Now, Hazen's going to ask you
to help coach.

95
00:11:29,120 --> 00:11:31,634
And you just tell him, "No way".

96
00:11:39,560 --> 00:11:40,879
Know something?

97
00:11:44,840 --> 00:11:46,831
I don't like you.

98
00:11:48,280 --> 00:11:50,555
You understand that?

99
00:11:50,760 --> 00:11:52,591
Oh, yeah.

100
00:11:55,040 --> 00:11:59,716
<i>Attention Cell Block 3 A. Please report
as scheduled to your period assignment,</i>

101
00:11:59,920 --> 00:12:02,229
<i>except for carpentry
and accounting classes.</i>

102
00:12:02,440 --> 00:12:07,798
<i>All men assigned to farm detail will
meet at one o'clock in the Rotunda.</i>

103
00:12:09,840 --> 00:12:13,037
Warden, Captain Knauer's here
with inmate Crewe.

104
00:12:13,760 --> 00:12:16,911
<i>- Send him in.
- Thank you, sir.</i>

105
00:12:18,320 --> 00:12:22,279
- You can go in now.
- Thank you, Miss Toot.

106
00:12:36,600 --> 00:12:38,397
Paul Crewe.

107
00:12:39,680 --> 00:12:41,511
The Wrecking Crewe.

108
00:12:44,720 --> 00:12:47,792
- It's good to have you here.
- Thank you.

109
00:12:51,160 --> 00:12:55,073
Young people can learn a great deal
from a skilful football game.

110
00:12:55,280 --> 00:12:59,751
Offence, defence,
spirit of achievement, teamwork.

111
00:13:04,680 --> 00:13:06,796
You might say...

112
00:13:12,080 --> 00:13:16,039
...the game embodies
what has made our country great.

113
00:13:17,040 --> 00:13:20,191
It's a great game.
It's played by great men.

114
00:13:23,320 --> 00:13:29,555
We have something of a football team
here ourselves, you know.

115
00:13:31,200 --> 00:13:34,636
First rank, semi-pro,
South-eastern League.

116
00:13:34,840 --> 00:13:38,150
Runner-up, National Champions,
past five years.

117
00:13:39,520 --> 00:13:43,308
Mister Crewe,
what do you think of semi-pro ball?

118
00:13:43,520 --> 00:13:45,556
Semi-pro's a joke.

119
00:13:49,640 --> 00:13:55,715
Well, perhaps we could use
a few pointers from the big leagues.

120
00:13:55,920 --> 00:14:00,596
Captain, what do you say
to Mister Crewe here looking in,

121
00:14:00,800 --> 00:14:03,678
giving us the benefit
of his invaluable knowledge?

122
00:14:04,200 --> 00:14:09,399
That's a real good idea, Warden.
We could use all the help we can get.

123
00:14:10,280 --> 00:14:11,952
Well?

124
00:14:12,160 --> 00:14:16,199
I haven't held a football in eight
years. I'm not in very good shape.

125
00:14:16,400 --> 00:14:19,153
Nobody's asked you to play,
Mister Crewe.

126
00:14:19,360 --> 00:14:23,956
What we need is a coach. New blood.

127
00:14:24,160 --> 00:14:25,878
New game plan.

128
00:14:30,720 --> 00:14:35,475
Anybody who was pro football's
Most Valuable Player is special,

129
00:14:35,680 --> 00:14:38,319
and I want to have that.

130
00:14:40,120 --> 00:14:42,031
I'm not interested in football anymore.

131
00:14:45,920 --> 00:14:49,993
Mister Crewe, I don't mind saying,

132
00:14:50,760 --> 00:14:53,228
I pulled a lot of strings
to get you down here.

133
00:14:54,240 --> 00:14:55,673
I appreciate that.

134
00:14:56,240 --> 00:14:58,151
Look.

135
00:14:58,360 --> 00:15:01,477
What I want is a national title.

136
00:15:02,800 --> 00:15:06,679
If, perchance, you should help us
achieve that goal,

137
00:15:06,880 --> 00:15:11,556
I expect your stay here
with us will be very agreeable.

138
00:15:13,000 --> 00:15:14,274
Well?

139
00:15:18,200 --> 00:15:22,159
I just want to do my time,
then get out of here.

140
00:15:23,160 --> 00:15:24,593
Very well.

141
00:15:30,760 --> 00:15:35,550
All right, I'll turn you over
to the good hands of Captain Knauer.

142
00:15:35,760 --> 00:15:37,352
Swamp reclamation.

143
00:15:39,120 --> 00:15:41,839
Get him out of here.

144
00:15:45,600 --> 00:15:47,830
- Captain.
- Yes, sir.

145
00:15:48,040 --> 00:15:49,837
I'd like a word with you.

146
00:15:52,480 --> 00:15:57,315
For the past five years,
you've promised me the national title,

147
00:15:57,520 --> 00:15:59,795
<i>and every year,
you've come up short.</i>

148
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:03,470
<i>- I try, sir.
- When I want an answer, I'll indicate.</i>

149
00:16:03,680 --> 00:16:05,477
<i>Yes, sir.</i>

150
00:16:05,680 --> 00:16:07,352
<i>You've asked for bonus money.</i>

151
00:16:07,560 --> 00:16:10,313
Certainly take their football
seriously, don't they?

152
00:16:10,760 --> 00:16:14,753
<i>This year you've asked for new
game uniforms. I've OK'ed them.</i>

153
00:16:15,400 --> 00:16:17,391
Everything you've asked for,
I've given you.

154
00:16:17,600 --> 00:16:20,319
Yes, sir. And I appreciate it, sir.

155
00:16:21,760 --> 00:16:24,149
I want that title.

156
00:16:24,360 --> 00:16:27,591
You'll give me that title,
or you'll be out of a job.

157
00:16:27,800 --> 00:16:31,156
You and all that
over-priced beef you call a team.

158
00:16:31,360 --> 00:16:34,033
We should be
in the Superbowl by now!

159
00:16:34,880 --> 00:16:38,873
<i>I've lost patience! The gravy train is
over! This year you're going to win!</i>

160
00:16:39,080 --> 00:16:40,399
You've lovely hair.

161
00:16:40,600 --> 00:16:45,435
<i>...your last chance! Prison is no
different from any other community.</i>

162
00:16:46,200 --> 00:16:49,112
Ever find any spiders in it?

163
00:16:49,320 --> 00:16:51,231
<i>...then I haven't done my job.</i>

164
00:16:51,720 --> 00:16:53,790
I'm not being unreasonable, am I?

165
00:16:54,680 --> 00:16:57,240
- No, sir.
- Then you'll give me the title?

166
00:16:57,440 --> 00:16:59,795
- Yes, sir.
- Good!

167
00:17:01,280 --> 00:17:03,669
I want that man out there.

168
00:17:03,880 --> 00:17:08,749
And I want you to make
that son of a bitch enthusiastic!

169
00:17:10,840 --> 00:17:14,469
- Ever do it standing up?
- Let's move it.

170
00:17:22,480 --> 00:17:26,109
- I say forget football, you do it.
- Why are you so mad?

171
00:17:26,320 --> 00:17:31,952
- You better start taking life seriously.
- I did exactly what you told me to do.

172
00:17:51,280 --> 00:17:53,794
Hey, Superstar.
Get a good night's sleep?

173
00:17:54,000 --> 00:17:56,150
Too bad you missed breakfast.
It was yummy!

174
00:17:57,240 --> 00:17:58,673
Gotta get it done.

175
00:17:58,880 --> 00:18:03,795
- This is make-work day.
- What's make-work day?

176
00:18:04,000 --> 00:18:06,230
You shovel it in
and shovel back out again.

177
00:18:06,440 --> 00:18:09,557
Hustle in there now.
Cover that bank.

178
00:18:09,760 --> 00:18:12,115
Get that wheelbarrow, Woody.

179
00:18:12,920 --> 00:18:14,638
Let's go. Single file.

180
00:18:14,840 --> 00:18:18,628
Hang it up, hang it up.
Let's get covered.

181
00:18:20,240 --> 00:18:23,437
All right, let's go. Come on.

182
00:18:23,640 --> 00:18:25,471
Get a shovel.

183
00:18:28,160 --> 00:18:29,559
Hey, Superstar.

184
00:18:32,120 --> 00:18:34,998
I got an idea. Granny.

185
00:18:41,120 --> 00:18:44,112
You ever work with a nigger before?

186
00:18:47,520 --> 00:18:49,272
Get another shovel there, boy.

187
00:18:55,880 --> 00:18:58,394
All right. Let's go.

188
00:19:04,080 --> 00:19:05,911
Heave it up!

189
00:19:07,280 --> 00:19:10,955
- Sitting down, boss?
- Not today, boy.

190
00:19:16,600 --> 00:19:20,673
- Wiping off, boss?
- Not today, boy.

191
00:19:22,360 --> 00:19:25,079
- Rolling one, boss?
- Not yet, boy.

192
00:19:26,280 --> 00:19:29,192
Now you know
how black man's work feels.

193
00:19:29,400 --> 00:19:30,879
How do you like it?

194
00:19:31,080 --> 00:19:33,230
Oh, it sort of grows on you.

195
00:19:33,440 --> 00:19:34,998
No talking there, Granny.

196
00:19:35,720 --> 00:19:40,157
- Yes, boss.
- You'll find yourselves in bad time.

197
00:19:40,360 --> 00:19:44,194
Yes, boss. Sorry about that, boss.

198
00:19:44,640 --> 00:19:47,279
What's he think this is, good time?

199
00:19:47,480 --> 00:19:51,837
Looky, looky, looky,
here comes cooky!

200
00:19:58,880 --> 00:20:03,510
Big deal. Look at him now.

201
00:20:06,200 --> 00:20:09,317
How do you like them apples,
Superstar?

202
00:20:12,960 --> 00:20:14,439
Move the line.

203
00:20:59,000 --> 00:21:00,956
Real friendly types
you got around here.

204
00:21:01,160 --> 00:21:04,869
- Might be your own fault.
- Oh, really?

205
00:21:05,080 --> 00:21:08,914
Most of these old boys have nothing.
Never had nothing to start with.

206
00:21:09,120 --> 00:21:12,749
But you, you had it all.

207
00:21:12,960 --> 00:21:16,396
Then you let your team-mates down,
got caught taking bribes.

208
00:21:17,200 --> 00:21:20,158
- I did, did I?
- I ain't saying either way.

209
00:21:20,360 --> 00:21:22,920
I'm just saying
you could've robbed banks, sold dope,

210
00:21:23,120 --> 00:21:26,635
stole your grandmother's pension,
and none of us would've minded.

211
00:21:26,840 --> 00:21:31,356
But shaving points off a football game,
that's un-American.

212
00:21:34,560 --> 00:21:36,551
You take football
real serious down here.

213
00:21:37,520 --> 00:21:40,796
- Mind if I ask you one question?
- Yeah, I do.

214
00:21:41,000 --> 00:21:42,991
Why'd you do it?

215
00:21:43,200 --> 00:21:47,876
- It's a long story.
- Well, I got eight years.

216
00:21:58,840 --> 00:22:02,150
Oh, my God.
What the hell is that?

217
00:22:02,360 --> 00:22:06,114
That's a member
of the warden's football team.

218
00:22:06,320 --> 00:22:10,074
Some of these guards are not
just everyday run-of-the-mill guards.

219
00:22:13,240 --> 00:22:16,437
Crewe! Granville! Front and centre.

220
00:22:16,640 --> 00:22:18,710
What now?

221
00:22:18,920 --> 00:22:23,232
That means we don't get
to finish this delicious lunch.

222
00:22:34,200 --> 00:22:35,553
What's he looking for?

223
00:22:36,840 --> 00:22:38,319
Snakes.

224
00:22:38,520 --> 00:22:40,795
- Snakes?
- Yeah.

225
00:22:49,720 --> 00:22:51,915
Take five!

226
00:23:00,720 --> 00:23:04,599
- Rolling one, boss?
- Not today, boy.

227
00:23:10,760 --> 00:23:12,159
Jeez!

228
00:23:25,640 --> 00:23:28,757
- Terrific.
- Football faggot!

229
00:23:31,720 --> 00:23:35,076
- Salt pill up here, boss?
- Go get it, boy.

230
00:23:35,880 --> 00:23:37,996
How long you been in this asylum,
Pop?

231
00:23:38,200 --> 00:23:39,792
Thirty-four years.

232
00:23:40,000 --> 00:23:42,116
- Thirty-four years?
- Yep.

233
00:23:42,320 --> 00:23:45,437
Last six and a half
right here in the swamp.

234
00:23:45,640 --> 00:23:49,030
Too old for reclamation,
so they made me barracks chief.

235
00:23:49,920 --> 00:23:52,673
Aren't you coming up
for parole soon?

236
00:23:52,880 --> 00:23:59,035
Thirty years ago, I made the mistake
of slugging a fish bull. Hazen.

237
00:24:00,120 --> 00:24:02,918
Just my luck he made warden.

238
00:24:03,120 --> 00:24:09,195
Sent me out here when I was 64 to die,
but I've been hanging on.

239
00:24:09,400 --> 00:24:14,110
