01:24:24,640 --> 01:24:27,916
will you call off the dogs?

965
01:24:31,360 --> 01:24:33,749
The dogs?

966
01:24:33,960 --> 01:24:38,795
If you've got the game in the bag,
you tell your guys to coast.

967
01:24:40,520 --> 01:24:43,876
I don't want any of my men hurt.

968
01:24:48,400 --> 01:24:50,675
You have my word.

969
01:24:50,880 --> 01:24:53,269
Once we get the 21 points.

970
01:24:57,200 --> 01:25:00,192
You know, there's only one thing
I'm sorry about.

971
01:25:00,400 --> 01:25:01,674
What's that?

972
01:25:01,880 --> 01:25:04,269
That you're not playing,
knocking heads.

973
01:25:07,000 --> 01:25:09,958
I'm afraid I'm a little
too old for that.

974
01:25:10,160 --> 01:25:13,755
No. You never had the guts
to begin with.

975
01:25:21,200 --> 01:25:25,193
You're playing like a bunch of girls.
Every one of you. Candy-asses.

976
01:25:26,920 --> 01:25:29,229
You know who's beating you out there?

977
01:25:29,440 --> 01:25:32,113
Scum's beating you out there. Scum.

978
01:25:32,320 --> 01:25:34,914
And that's the lowest
part of the world.

979
01:25:35,120 --> 01:25:38,032
Those are the criminals
and rapists. The murderers.

980
01:25:38,240 --> 01:25:39,912
You're supposed
to represent law and order.

981
01:25:40,880 --> 01:25:43,678
- You're supposed to...
- Listen to this shit.

982
01:25:43,880 --> 01:25:45,393
He thinks he's Rockne.

983
01:25:45,600 --> 01:25:47,238
You're letting the flag down.

984
01:25:47,440 --> 01:25:51,319
Go out there and do something about it.
Offence and defence play together.

985
01:25:51,520 --> 01:25:54,432
Let's go now. Come on!

986
01:26:11,080 --> 01:26:14,516
- You're guaranteed a 21-point spread.
- What?

987
01:26:14,720 --> 01:26:17,678
Because of your performance,
I was forced to make a deal.

988
01:26:18,560 --> 01:26:20,596
In the second half we can beat them.

989
01:26:20,800 --> 01:26:24,429
I don't care what you think.
You'll do as I told you.

990
01:26:24,640 --> 01:26:26,358
Mister Crewe will do the same.

991
01:26:26,600 --> 01:26:27,874
Yes, sir.

992
01:26:30,200 --> 01:26:33,875
When you and your mental midgets
are 21 points ahead,

993
01:26:34,080 --> 01:26:38,392
I want you to inflict as much painful
damage on the prisoners as possible.

994
01:26:40,240 --> 01:26:43,437
So you understand,
before this game is over,

995
01:26:43,640 --> 01:26:49,158
I want every prisoner in this institution
to know what I mean by power,

996
01:26:49,360 --> 01:26:51,590
and who controls it.

997
01:26:53,160 --> 01:26:55,993
Do we understand each other?

998
01:26:56,200 --> 01:26:58,555
Yes, sir.

999
01:27:04,080 --> 01:27:05,354
<i>It's 15- 13</i>

1000
01:27:05,560 --> 01:27:11,556
<i>and the second half of a surprisingly
close ball game is about to begin.</i>

1001
01:27:14,560 --> 01:27:17,711
<i>...ball goes down
and is taken by number 36.</i>

1002
01:27:25,520 --> 01:27:28,193
Set! Hut!

1003
01:27:28,400 --> 01:27:31,676
<i>...goes straight back, he's getting good
protection and is looking for the receiver.</i>

1004
01:27:31,880 --> 01:27:34,269
Throw the ball, man.
I'm open. Crewe!

1005
01:27:34,920 --> 01:27:36,194
Crewe!

1006
01:27:38,680 --> 01:27:40,238
Crewe!

1007
01:27:42,120 --> 01:27:44,111
Crewe! Oh, shit!

1008
01:27:46,680 --> 01:27:50,468
- I own that hamburger. Pass it.
- I was open. Can't you see?

1009
01:27:50,680 --> 01:27:52,113
Enough. I'm calling the plays.

1010
01:27:56,680 --> 01:27:58,193
Hut!

1011
01:28:13,080 --> 01:28:15,435
<i>First and ten for the Guards
in opposition territory.</i>

1012
01:28:15,640 --> 01:28:17,437
All right. No sweat.

1013
01:28:17,640 --> 01:28:19,790
<i>Crewe has been poor
in this last series of plays.</i>

1014
01:28:20,000 --> 01:28:21,991
<i>Something seems
to have happened to him.</i>

1015
01:28:22,200 --> 01:28:25,670
<i>That last pass wasjust not
a Paul Crewe pass.</i>

1016
01:28:26,400 --> 01:28:28,755
Come on, we'll get it back.

1017
01:28:36,160 --> 01:28:37,673
<i>Touchdown!</i>

1018
01:28:45,040 --> 01:28:46,837
Stick it to 'em. He's going to choke.

1019
01:28:51,040 --> 01:28:55,238
<i>Paul Crewe looking to pass.
Gets a pass off and it's short.</i>

1020
01:28:55,440 --> 01:28:57,715
<i>It's short and it's picked off
by number 21.</i>

1021
01:29:00,440 --> 01:29:02,158
We got it! We got it!

1022
01:29:02,640 --> 01:29:06,553
<i>It's another touchdown for the Guards,
bringing their score to 28,</i>

1023
01:29:06,760 --> 01:29:08,591
<i>to thirteen for the Mean Machine.</i>

1024
01:29:10,880 --> 01:29:12,711
- What's happening?
- I'm having a bad day.

1025
01:29:12,920 --> 01:29:16,276
- Bad day?
- Yes. Have you never had one?

1026
01:29:16,480 --> 01:29:18,789
Get off my back.

1027
01:29:22,480 --> 01:29:25,392
Set! Hut!

1028
01:29:26,720 --> 01:29:30,952
<i>- Ball snaps back and there's a fumble...
- Fumble, fumble!</i>

1029
01:29:31,160 --> 01:29:34,197
- What is that?
- You call yourself good!

1030
01:29:34,400 --> 01:29:37,836
Why did you change uniform?
Bullshit.

1031
01:29:41,600 --> 01:29:44,717
Paul Crewe
is taking himself out of the ball game.

1032
01:29:45,400 --> 01:29:49,109
<i>Paul Crewe is limping badly.
He's limping off the field.</i>

1033
01:29:49,320 --> 01:29:52,153
Pop Steadman's
bringing him to the bench.

1034
01:29:52,360 --> 01:29:55,511
<i>We may have seen
the last of Paul Crewe for today.</i>

1035
01:30:06,720 --> 01:30:10,793
Let's get this shoe off
and look at that ankle.

1036
01:30:11,000 --> 01:30:14,390
I could give him one of my empis.
I'd knock his head off.

1037
01:30:14,600 --> 01:30:16,318
I could be inside making wallets.

1038
01:30:16,520 --> 01:30:21,310
Doesn't feel broken. Somebody
step on it or did you twist it?

1039
01:30:21,520 --> 01:30:24,592
- Twisted it.
- Golden boy? Superstar?

1040
01:30:25,480 --> 01:30:28,790
To think we fought Granny for this crap.

1041
01:30:29,000 --> 01:30:31,309
Really sold us out, didn't you, Crewe?

1042
01:30:31,520 --> 01:30:34,273
Anybody can see
he's throwing the game.

1043
01:30:34,480 --> 01:30:36,630
<i>Pull 'em down, go, let's go.</i>

1044
01:30:37,920 --> 01:30:39,399
Let's go.

1045
01:30:39,600 --> 01:30:43,229
<i>...at the line of scrimmage.
Less than an inch for a touchdown.</i>

1046
01:30:43,440 --> 01:30:46,477
<i>The ball is going back to Keller...</i>

1047
01:30:47,360 --> 01:30:51,558
<i>A touchdown for the Guards,
making the score 35 to 13.</i>

1048
01:30:53,000 --> 01:30:57,869
<i>With 5 minutes 58 left in the third
quarter, which has been all Guardsmen,</i>

1049
01:30:58,640 --> 01:31:05,512
<i>the score is 35 for the Guardsmen
and 13 for the Mean Machine.</i>

1050
01:31:06,760 --> 01:31:08,034
No point.

1051
01:31:08,480 --> 01:31:10,596
<i>With 5.58 left in the third period,</i>

1052
01:31:10,800 --> 01:31:15,396
<i>the score remains 35 for the Guardsmen
and 13 for the Mean Machine.</i>

1053
01:31:17,160 --> 01:31:21,836
Kill that Indian mother! Get that
Indian by the boots! Get him over!

1054
01:31:23,880 --> 01:31:28,829
Good blocking.
Keep it up. Keep it up.

1055
01:31:29,040 --> 01:31:30,314
Come on now.

1056
01:31:31,480 --> 01:31:35,678
<i>Guards'ball, third and two
on their own 37-yard line.</i>

1057
01:31:37,440 --> 01:31:40,318
<i>Knauer takes the pass
and throws it to Levitt...</i>

1058
01:31:40,520 --> 01:31:45,594
<i>...Levitt takes the ball and he's going
to the Mean Machine 30-yard line...</i>

1059
01:31:46,880 --> 01:31:50,077
...on me.
Jesus Christ! Another injury.

1060
01:31:50,280 --> 01:31:52,555
Come on.

1061
01:31:52,760 --> 01:31:57,959
<i>...number 74, Shop Steward, is badly
hurt, bleeding badly from the mouth.</i>

1062
01:31:58,160 --> 01:32:01,709
<i>...ball goes back to Knauer, who
hands off 11 for another long gain.</i>

1063
01:32:02,640 --> 01:32:04,312
<i>...another injury...</i>

1064
01:32:05,000 --> 01:32:10,950
<i>...and it's Sonny Tannen.
He seems to be badly shaken up.</i>

1065
01:32:15,720 --> 01:32:17,870
Crybaby son of a bitch!

1066
01:32:21,120 --> 01:32:22,951
Time! Another man down.

1067
01:32:29,040 --> 01:32:34,990
Superstar, what kind of deal did you
make this time? What did Hazen promise?

1068
01:32:35,800 --> 01:32:40,749
They're killing those guys out there
and you don't even care.

1069
01:32:47,200 --> 01:32:51,273
He's right, Crewe.
You fooled the hell out of me.

1070
01:32:51,480 --> 01:32:53,596
I trusted you
and you let me down.

1071
01:32:54,920 --> 01:32:59,755
I know you don't give a shit about nothing,
but I didn't think you'd sell us out.

1072
01:33:00,440 --> 01:33:04,752
Granny,
better get back in there.

1073
01:33:09,600 --> 01:33:12,512
Four three inside flank.
Ready? Break.

1074
01:33:15,600 --> 01:33:17,670
<i>Ball's on the Mean Machine
48-yard line.</i>

1075
01:33:17,880 --> 01:33:21,156
<i>...ball's gone to Knauer,
he hands off 44...</i>

1076
01:33:22,600 --> 01:33:23,999
<i>...he's picking one up...</i>

1077
01:33:34,880 --> 01:33:36,757
- What is it?
- Broken collarbone.

1078
01:33:36,960 --> 01:33:38,916
- You sure?
- I'm sure.

1079
01:33:39,120 --> 01:33:44,114
<i>Officials are trying to break up that
fight, getting pretty rough in there.</i>

1080
01:33:47,760 --> 01:33:52,709
<i>Granny Granville is hurt. He's holding
his shoulder and appears to be badly hurt.</i>

1081
01:33:52,920 --> 01:33:56,674
<i>Probably a broken bone,
but he is on his feet.</i>

1082
01:33:58,880 --> 01:34:00,836
Satisfied now?

1083
01:34:04,960 --> 01:34:06,234
Jesus, Sonny!

1084
01:34:06,440 --> 01:34:11,275
<i>The officials will assess the penalty.
15 yards for unsporting conduct.</i>

1085
01:34:16,040 --> 01:34:17,837
- Hey, Pop.
- Yeah?

1086
01:34:19,000 --> 01:34:22,549
That time you hit Hazen in the mouth,
was it worth it?

1087
01:34:23,480 --> 01:34:27,234
Was it worth 30 years?

1088
01:34:27,440 --> 01:34:29,556
Yeah. For me it was.

1089
01:34:32,720 --> 01:34:35,314
Well, give me my goddamn shoe.

1090
01:34:41,640 --> 01:34:42,914
<i>Wait a minute.</i>

1091
01:34:43,120 --> 01:34:48,956
<i>Paul Crewe, number 22, is going back
into the game for the Mean Machine.</i>

1092
01:34:49,160 --> 01:34:54,951
All right. New quarterback. Shok, you're
on the bench. Move over. Here we go.

1093
01:34:55,800 --> 01:34:59,349
- Makes no difference where you go.
- Fuck you.

1094
01:34:59,560 --> 01:35:01,790
Look who's back.
It's the baby boy.

1095
01:35:05,320 --> 01:35:09,552
- Set!
- Set, my ass.

1096
01:35:11,400 --> 01:35:12,958
What is he trying to pull?

1097
01:35:13,480 --> 01:35:15,994
- Hut!
- Uh-uh.

1098
01:35:16,200 --> 01:35:19,431
Get that Superstar.

1099
01:35:19,640 --> 01:35:21,915
<i>Behind the line of scrimmage
for a six-yard goal.</i>

1100
01:35:25,160 --> 01:35:30,109
Show 'em who's boss.
Get them. They ain't shit.

1101
01:35:33,280 --> 01:35:34,872
That's how it is?

1102
01:35:35,080 --> 01:35:38,993
<i>They're in a huddle now. There's
the gun ending the third quarter.</i>

1103
01:35:40,080 --> 01:35:43,072
That's the quarter.
Let's change ends.

1104
01:35:46,920 --> 01:35:50,071
<i>Ball goes to Crewe. He's going to
pass on fourth and long-yard it.</i>

1105
01:35:50,280 --> 01:35:52,077
<i>...holds the ball
and goes up the middle.</i>

1106
01:35:52,280 --> 01:35:53,554
<i>Crewe goes up the middle...</i>

1107
01:35:59,000 --> 01:36:00,752
That's it, Paul.

1108
01:36:04,280 --> 01:36:06,748
<i>- The line is set...
- Hut!</i>

1109
01:36:06,960 --> 01:36:11,909
<i>...he's going up the centre.</i>

1110
01:36:15,720 --> 01:36:17,438
Shotgun left. Shotgun.

1111
01:36:20,320 --> 01:36:22,356
Hut! Hut!

1112
01:36:23,200 --> 01:36:26,875
<i>Crewe's looking for a receiver.</i>

1113
01:36:34,480 --> 01:36:35,754
Where's he going?

1114
01:36:36,240 --> 01:36:39,471
<i>There's a figure that graced
the Polo Grounds for years.</i>

1115
01:36:41,360 --> 01:36:43,954
What are you guys so surprised about?

1116
01:36:44,160 --> 01:36:46,594
I'm not letting you have all the fun.

1117
01:36:47,400 --> 01:36:50,233
Bootleg on one.
Ready? Break.

1118
01:36:51,040 --> 01:36:54,919
OK. Come on.
Looks good. Keep it alive.

1119
01:36:57,120 --> 01:36:58,599
Set!

1120
01:37:00,920 --> 01:37:02,638
Hut!

1121
01:37:09,760 --> 01:37:12,274
<i>There's a first down
on the 20-yard line.</i>

1122
01:37:15,520 --> 01:37:16,794
Your confidence back?

1123
01:37:17,720 --> 01:37:20,359
- Get Scarboro.
- Son of a bitch.

1124
01:37:23,480 --> 01:37:27,758
<i>Ball goes back to Crewe,
he's waiting to pass...</i>

1125
01:37:40,040 --> 01:37:44,238
<i>...by Bogdanski. Bogdanski hit
Nate Scarboro a cheap shot.</i>

1126
01:37:44,440 --> 01:37:46,396
<i>A reprehensible action.</i>

1127
01:37:47,000 --> 01:37:48,752
Cheap shot!

1128
01:37:51,240 --> 01:37:53,117
Let me at the son of a bitch.

1129
01:37:55,560 --> 01:37:58,870
Old Double O
is down and seems badly hurt.

1130
01:37:59,880 --> 01:38:01,757
How is it, Nate?

1131
01:38:01,960 --> 01:38:06,670
I love it. After all these years,
my first touchdown.

1132
01:38:07,480 --> 01:38:10,119
It's got to be his knee.
I heard it pop.

1133
01:38:11,160 --> 01:38:13,879
- Get him up.
- You'll be OK. Hang in there.

1134
01:38:21,280 --> 01:38:23,555
Hey, Paul. You've got to do it.

1135
01:38:25,920 --> 01:38:28,878
- Screw Hazen!
- Don't worry. He'll get his.

1136
01:38:31,080 --> 01:38:32,798
<i>Good old Nate Scarboro.</i>

1137
01:38:33,000 --> 01:38:35,878
One of the most beloved men
this institution has had.

1138
01:38:47,560 --> 01:38:50,632
<i>The extra point kick is good.</i>

1139
01:38:50,840 --> 01:38:53,718
<i>Tightening that score now
to 35 to 20.</i>

1140
01:38:55,160 --> 01:38:59,358
Blue Eyes can kick the ball ten yards,
can someone fall on it?

1141
01:38:59,560 --> 01:39:02,472
- Right on.
- Then let's go!

1142
01:39:08,160 --> 01:39:11,152
<i>Charlie Blue Eyes approaches the ball
and kicks...</i>

1143
01:39:11,360 --> 01:39:13,555
<i>It's an on-side kick...</i>

1144
01:39:19,520 --> 01:39:22,432
<i>And it's recovered
for the Mean Machine.</i>

1145
01:39:25,400 --> 01:39:28,039
Shut up. Shut up!

1146
01:39:28,240 --> 01:39:30,071
You're stinking the place up.

1147
01:39:30,680 --> 01:39:33,717
- Can we take 'em?
- Yeah!

1148
01:39:38,240 --> 01:39:41,232
Split right. On two. Ready?

1149
01:39:49,640 --> 01:39:51,153
Set!

1150
01:39:52,520 --> 01:39:54,078
Hut!

1151
01:39:54,280 --> 01:39:57,875
<i>Ball goes back to Crewe.
Crewe hands off to number 30...</i>

1152
01:40:05,400 --> 01:40:08,153
<i>...23 yards.
Crewe's down on the ten-yard line.</i>

1153
01:40:08,360 --> 01:40:10,032
A beautiful piece of razzle-dazzle.

1154
01:40:10,760 --> 01:40:16,073
<i>Paul Crewe reached into
his bag of tricks that time, folks.</i>

1155
01:40:29,440 --> 01:40:33,797
<i>Charlie Blue Eyes splits the uprights
and that makes it 35 to 27.</i>

1156
01:40:34,000 --> 01:40:36,719
- How we doing?
- Fine.

1157
01:40:36,920 --> 01:40:39,275
There you go, Nate.

1158
01:40:39,480 --> 01:40:42,950
I heard you were on your way in.

1159
01:40:45,840 --> 01:40:48,832
Hey, did they tell you
about my touchdown?

1160
01:40:49,040 --> 01:40:53,431
<i>We repeat, with five minutes and
four seconds left in the fourth quarter,</i>

1161
01:40:53,640 --> 01:40:56,074
<i>there is now only
an eight-point difference.</i>

1162
01:41:00,720 --> 01:41:03,837
- Here we go.
- Can you drop-kick from here?

1163
01:41:04,040 --> 01:41:06,110
- I could try.
- Drop-kick?

1164
01:41:07,040 --> 01:41:09,110
It's fourth and four
and we're going to drop-kick.

1165
01:41:09,320 --> 01:41:13,029
Shotgun.
Drop-kick, on one. Ready?

1166
01:41:18,080 --> 01:41:20,435
<i>...he's got to come up
with something different.</i>

1167
01:41:22,400 --> 01:41:24,630
<i>Ball goes back to
Charlie Blue Eyes...</i>

1168
01:41:29,760 --> 01:41:31,591
I haven't seen one
of those in years.

1169
01:41:32,480 --> 01:41:35,074
- What was that?
- A drop-kick.

1170
01:41:35,280 --> 01:41:38,511
- How much does that count?
- Three points.

1171
01:41:38,920 --> 01:41:41,957
For that? Bullshit!

1172
01:41:43,760 --> 01:41:46,832
<i>The score stands Guards 35,
Mean Machine 30.</i>

1173
01:41:47,040 --> 01:41:50,316
<i>Fourth and 21
for the Mean Machine on their own 39.</i>

1174
01:41:50,520 --> 01:41:53,034
<i>Crewe is feigning...</i>

1175
01:41:53,240 --> 01:41:55,708
<i>...and he dumps off another pass.</i>

1176
01:42:04,880 --> 01:42:07,269
<i>...Bogdanski saves a touchdown.</i>

1177
01:42:07,480 --> 01:42:10,995
Bogdanski is really wreaking havoc
on that Mean Machine team.

1178
01:42:14,000 --> 01:42:16,434
Quiet down.
Now, listen to me.

1179
01:42:17,120 --> 01:42:20,795
We're going to let Bogdanski come right
through. Nobody touch him. Got it?

1180
01:42:21,000 --> 01:42:25,676
I want to try something.
If it works, everybody hit him. Right?

1181
01:42:25,880 --> 01:42:30,874
- Right.
- Split right. All curl, on one. Ready?

1182
01:42:31,640 --> 01:42:32,914
Red left!

1183
01:42:33,400 --> 01:42:36,039
Blue 69!

1184
01:42:36,480 --> 01:42:38,596
Blue 69!

1185
01:42:40,200 --> 01:42:41,792
Set!

1186
01:42:45,880 --> 01:42:49,111
<i>...throws the ball
directly at Bogdanski's groin.</i>

1187
01:42:53,080 --> 01:42:55,355
- Get off him.
- That's bullshit!

1188
01:42:57,600 --> 01:43:00,114
<i>They're unravelling the tangle now,</i>

1189
01:43:00,320 --> 01:43:03,676
and there's a penalty against
the Mean Machine for roughness,

1190
01:43:03,880 --> 01:43:09,113
<i>and that pass sure didn't look like
it was an accident.</i>

1191
01:43:09,600 --> 01:43:13,878
Bogdanski is staggering,
but he is up and on his feet.

1192
01:43:14,080 --> 01:43:19,552
OK. We've got fifteenth.
Let's huddle up on the ball. Huddle up.

1193
01:43:26,240 --> 01:43:27,514
Unbelievable.

1194
01:43:36,200 --> 01:43:38,031
Hey, Bog.
Get out of here.

1195
01:43:38,240 --> 01:43:40,435
- Come on.
- I know what I'm doing.

1196
01:43:40,640 --> 01:43:44,474
- Worked once, got to work again. Right?
- Right.

1197
01:43:44,680 --> 01:43:48,958
All right.
One more time, on two. Ready?

1198
01:43:49,160 --> 01:43:53,119
<i>It's third and 32
for the Mean Machine.</i>

1199
01:43:59,080 --> 01:44:01,469
Set!
Hut!

1200
01:44:01,680 --> 01:44:03,910
<i>Ball goes back to Crewe...</i>

1201
01:44:05,440 --> 01:44:08,034
Crewe hits Bogdanski with the ball
right in the...

1202
01:44:08,240 --> 01:44:10,629
<i>...in the nether regions.</i>

1203
01:44:10,840 --> 01:44:14,469
<i>Once again, Bogdanski is down,
the Mean Machine is dirty.</i>

1204
01:44:29,480 --> 01:44:32,438
- He's not breathing.
- Do something. Try mouth-to-mouth.

1205
01:44:33,040 --> 01:44:36,794
- You want to?
- No way.

1206
01:44:37,360 --> 01:44:38,679
Ambulance. Help!

1207
01:44:40,520 --> 01:44:45,878
<i>They are taking Bogdanski
off the field in an ambulance.</i>

1208
01:45:09,680 --> 01:45:11,875
He pushed him!

1209
01:45:16,360 --> 01:45:19,636
You can't see,
you blind son of a bitch.

1210
01:45:19,840 --> 01:45:24,118
Hey, Walking Boss,
here's your crying towel.

1211
01:45:24,320 --> 01:45:27,198
You big fat-assed son of a bitch.

1212
01:45:27,400 --> 01:45:30,790
Go get off and stay off.

1213
01:45:31,000 --> 01:45:32,433
First down.

1214
01:45:33,280 --> 01:45:34,554
Time out.

1215
01:45:34,760 --> 01:45:36,352
Jesus!

1216
01:45:38,720 --> 01:45:41,678
- Scooter, you want to hit somebody?
- Yeah.

1217
01:45:41,880 --> 01:45:44,792
All right. Tackle eligible.

1218
01:45:45,000 --> 01:45:46,831
Mawabe, talk to me.

1219
01:45:47,040 --> 01:45:49,508
- What are you doing?
- One step off the line.

1220
01:45:49,720 --> 01:45:51,950
- I'll step on the line.
- Right. On one. Ready?

1221
01:45:52,160 --> 01:45:57,188
Machine's ball, first and ten
on the Guards' 31-yard line.

1222
01:45:57,400 --> 01:45:58,833
Blue 28!

1223
01:45:59,040 --> 01:46:01,952
<i>...less than one minute
57 seconds left.</i>

1224
01:46:02,720 --> 01:46:04,278
Hut!

1225
01:46:11,480 --> 01:46:13,198
Protest that play!

1226
01:46:23,520 --> 01:46:24,953
Crewe, call time.

1227
01:46:25,600 --> 01:46:28,876
Time. Time.
Time, ref. Time.

1228
01:46:29,080 --> 01:46:31,878
<i>First and goal on the one-yard line,</i>

1229
01:46:32,080 --> 01:46:34,036
as Crewe calls time out, with...

1230
01:46:34,240 --> 01:46:37,152
<i>...40 seconds left on the clock.</i>

1231
01:46:37,360 --> 01:46:39,828
Mean Machine! Mean Machine!

1232
01:46:40,040 --> 01:46:43,430
Mean Machine! Mean Machine!

1233
01:46:43,640 --> 01:46:45,358
Mean Machine!

1234
01:46:47,800 --> 01:46:50,234
Quiet down. Split right...
Joe Jack!

1235
01:46:50,440 --> 01:46:53,273
Split right, sweep left.
On one. Ready?

1236
01:46:55,200 --> 01:46:58,397
Blue 28! Blue 28!

1237
01:46:58,600 --> 01:47:00,352
Set! Hut!

1238
01:47:07,440 --> 01:47:10,034
<i>Ladies and gentlemen,
this is really a ball game.</i>

1239
01:47:10,240 --> 01:47:12,276
This is a great ball team.

1240
01:47:12,480 --> 01:47:16,439
<i>They're giving these Guardsmen
the fight of their lives.</i>

1241
01:47:19,800 --> 01:47:23,156
Split right, roll out right,
option pass. Be waiting, Mace.

1242
01:47:23,360 --> 01:47:25,396
On two, on two. Ready?

1243
01:47:25,600 --> 01:47:28,558
<i>- Second and goal.
- Blue 20.</i>

1244
01:47:29,720 --> 01:47:33,429
Blue 20. Set! Hut!

1245
01:47:34,920 --> 01:47:36,399
<i>Crewe feigns the pass...</i>

1246
01:47:37,080 --> 01:47:40,072
<i>...and he throws...</i>

1247
01:47:40,280 --> 01:47:43,909
...stopping the clock again
with 16 seconds left.

1248
01:47:46,840 --> 01:47:49,229
Flip right, dive left, Indian.

1249
01:47:49,440 --> 01:47:52,000
Now, if we don't make it,
everybody yell time.

1250
01:47:52,200 --> 01:47:54,031
Everybody yell time.
On one. Ready?

1251
01:47:59,760 --> 01:48:03,719
Blue 29! Blue 29!
Set!

1252
01:48:04,720 --> 01:48:07,154
<i>Ball goes back to Crewe...</i>

1253
01:48:10,040 --> 01:48:13,396
Time! Time!

1254
01:48:13,760 --> 01:48:16,479
Crewe calls for his third
and last time out

1255
01:48:16,680 --> 01:48:18,955
<i>with seven seconds left on the clock.</i>

1256
01:48:19,600 --> 01:48:21,670
Mean Machine! Mean Machine!

1257
01:48:23,680 --> 01:48:25,432
Where the hell's he going?

1258
01:48:26,640 --> 01:48:27,959
Let's find out.

1259
01:48:28,840 --> 01:48:33,197
<i>Crewe has taken his last time out
and he's heading toward the bench.</i>

1260
01:48:33,400 --> 01:48:38,315
<i>He's heading toward the bench
followed by his entire offensive unit.</i>

1261
01:48:39,440 --> 01:48:40,759
<i>Most unusual...</i>

1262
01:48:41,800 --> 01:48:45,156
<i>I don't know what they're doing,
it's silent as a church.</i>

1263
01:48:46,080 --> 01:48:49,789
<i>It looks more like a prayer meeting
than a huddle.</i>

1264
01:48:50,000 --> 01:48:52,230
<i>Whatever happens,
regardless of the outcome,</i>

1265
01:48:52,440 --> 01:48:55,477
<i>this has been one fantastic showing.</i>

1266
01:48:55,680 --> 01:48:58,399
We've come too far together
to stop now.

1267
01:48:58,600 --> 01:49:01,797
For Granny, for Nate,

1268
01:49:04,520 --> 01:49:08,274
for Caretaker, let's do it.

1269
01:49:16,080 --> 01:49:18,389
Mean Machine!

1270
01:49:21,240 --> 01:49:22,832
Mean Machine!

1271
01:49:25,680 --> 01:49:28,513
Mean Machine! Mean Machine!

1272
01:49:40,440 --> 01:49:43,318
- Hold it down!
- Cool it!

1273
01:49:44,640 --> 01:49:47,154
Set!

1274
01:49:48,520 --> 01:49:50,431
Hut!

1275
01:51:17,160 --> 01:51:21,551
<i>Thirty-six, thirty-five,
in favour of the Mean Machine.</i>

1276
01:51:29,800 --> 01:51:31,074
<i>Ladies and gentlemen,</i>

1277
01:51:31,280 --> 01:51:33,350
<i>like the fabled phoenix of old...</i>

1278
01:51:44,840 --> 01:51:47,229
Mean Machine! Mean Machine!

1279
01:51:47,440 --> 01:51:50,830
Mean Machine! Mean Machine!

1280
01:51:51,040 --> 01:51:54,555
Mean Machine! Mean Machine!

1281
01:51:54,760 --> 01:51:56,751
Mean Machine! Mean Machine!

1282
01:52:19,920 --> 01:52:26,029
- You know, you guys ain't half bad.
- You're right.

1283
01:52:27,680 --> 01:52:29,113
Fuck you, boy.

1284
01:52:29,680 --> 01:52:32,114
Not today, boss.

1285
01:52:40,040 --> 01:52:42,713
History.

1286
01:52:42,920 --> 01:52:46,993
We stopped 'em. We are number one!

1287
01:52:55,960 --> 01:52:59,111
Where's your goddamn
power theory now?

1288
01:52:59,320 --> 01:53:01,231
He's trying to escape.

1289
01:53:01,440 --> 01:53:04,079
- Oh, shit!
- Officer!

1290
01:53:04,280 --> 01:53:06,191
- Crewe!
- I'm talking to you!

1291
01:53:08,800 --> 01:53:10,074
Crewe!

1292
01:53:10,280 --> 01:53:12,589
He's trying to escape. Shoot him!

1293
01:53:13,200 --> 01:53:16,158
- Crewe!
- You going to let him escape? Shoot.

1294
01:53:16,360 --> 01:53:19,033
- Shoot him, you... Shoot him!
- Crewe!

1295
01:53:20,400 --> 01:53:24,473
- Crewe!
- Kill him! Kill that son of a bitch!

1296
01:53:24,680 --> 01:53:26,272
Shoot him!

1297
01:53:45,640 --> 01:53:47,870
Game ball.

1298
01:54:02,200 --> 01:54:04,475
Stick this in your trophy case.

1299
01:54:10,680 --> 01:54:13,194
I knew you could do it!

